From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai>
Date: Thu, 12 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] drm/cix/linlon-dp: fix symbol clashes and clang -Werror issues

When allyesconfig builds both DRM komeda and CIX linlon-dp as built-in,
linking vmlinux fails due to duplicate global helper symbols copied from
komeda into linlon-dp.

Also fix clang -Werror failures seen in allyesconfig/allmodconfig paths by
keeping config-dependent locals/helpers scoped to the build path that uses
them, cleaning up misleading indentation, and fixing linlondp plane/crtc
prototype and CLOCK_FIXED-path unused-variable diagnostics.

These changes keep runtime behavior unchanged while removing link-time and
compile-time failures across aggressive build matrices.

